# Telegram
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=your_bot_token_here
TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID=your_chat_id_here

# Data providers
# Optional but recommended: without it, quotes/news fall back to Yahoo, and
# fundamentals/financial-statement data (/fundamentals, and the fundamentals
# section in /check and /recommend) is unavailable entirely — Yahoo has no
# usable equivalent (its fundamentals endpoint requires a crumb/cookie
# handshake we don't implement). Leave this line blank/unset if you don't
# have a key — do NOT leave a placeholder string here, a non-empty value is
# treated as "configured" even if invalid.
FINNHUB_API_KEY=your_finnhub_key_here

# Optional: Taiwan-market fundamentals (PER/PBR/dividend yield, quarterly
# EPS/revenue/gross margin, month-revenue YoY — see internal/data/finmind.go)
# via FinMind's free API. Leave blank/unset to disable — a TW ticker's
# /fundamentals and the fundamentals section in /check and /recommend simply
# have no data, same nil-degrade convention as FINNHUB_API_KEY above. Get a
# free token at https://finmindtrade.com/analysis/#/login (600 req/hr).
FINMIND_TOKEN=your_finmind_token_here

# LLM
# Uses your Claude Pro/Max subscription via the local `claude` CLI login
# instead of a billed API key. Run `claude` once on this machine and sign in
# before starting the bot; no ANTHROPIC_API_KEY is needed (and must NOT be
# set here or in your shell env, or the ACP agent will bill your API account
# instead of using the subscription). Requires Node.js (npx) to be installed.
# Model aliases: "opus", "sonnet", "haiku", or a full model ID. Leave unset
# to use the agent's own default.
CLAUDE_RECOMMEND_MODEL=opus
CLAUDE_CHECK_MODEL=sonnet
CLAUDE_CHAT_MODEL=sonnet
# Optional: point at a globally-installed `claude-agent-acp` binary instead
# of paying npx's resolution overhead on every call:
#   npm install -g @agentclientprotocol/claude-agent-acp
# CLAUDE_ACP_COMMAND=claude-agent-acp

# Optional Antigravity fallback (used only if every Claude call fails, e.g.
# usage cap hit). Uses your Google Antigravity subscription via OAuth login
# to the `agy` CLI, no API key. Off by default and NOT a drop-in-safe
# feature: `agy`'s non-interactive mode has no read-only equivalent and will
# auto-approve any tool call it decides to make, so this always runs with
# --sandbox to contain that to an isolated container rather than the host —
# read AntigravityProvider's doc comment in internal/llm before enabling.
# Requires the VPS to have a working sandbox/container runtime for `agy`.
# ANTIGRAVITY_ENABLED=true
# ANTIGRAVITY_MODEL=

# Exit discipline (Phase 3.8, daily-report only — no intraday/at-price
# monitoring). Positive percentages; set either to 0 to disable that check.
# STOP_LOSS_PCT alerts once when a position's unrealized loss crosses this
# threshold (default below the cost basis). TRAILING_STOP_PCT alerts once
# when the price falls this far from the highest close since the position
# was first opened. Both dedup via signal_states: they alert once per
# breach and reset once the position recovers back above the threshold.
STOP_LOSS_PCT=10
TRAILING_STOP_PCT=15

# Optional ATR(14)-based trailing-stop distance (Phase 3.8 追加項, see
# docs/phase-3.8-atr-trailing-stop.md). Default 0 disables it — behavior is
# then identical to before this setting existed. When > 0, the effective
# threshold becomes min(TRAILING_STOP_PCT, TRAILING_STOP_ATR_MULT x ATR(14) /
# peak x 100): TRAILING_STOP_PCT still caps worst-case drawdown tolerance,
# while the ATR-based distance tightens it for lower-volatility tickers.
# 3 is the textbook chandelier-exit multiplier. Falls back to
# TRAILING_STOP_PCT alone when ATR can't be computed for a ticker.
# TRAILING_STOP_ATR_MULT=3

# Optional R-based position-sizing suggestion on BUY recommendations (Phase
# 3.11 PR1, see docs/phase-3.11-trade-risk-management.md). Default 0/unset
# disables the feature entirely — no sizing line is shown. When set (e.g.
# 1.0 = risk at most 1% of account value per trade), each BUY recommendation
# with a computable ATR(14) gets a bot-computed suggested share count
# (account value = latest net worth snapshot + declared /cash balance, stop
# reference = price - 2xATR14). Never sent to the LLM to compute — this is
# deterministic Go arithmetic only.
# RISK_PCT_PER_TRADE=1.0

# Storage
DB_PATH=data/argus.db
# Log file, rotated daily at midnight (Taiwan time) and kept for ~7 days.
LOG_PATH=data/argus.log
# Daily SQLite backup (VACUUM INTO, 06:00 Taiwan time) and how many days of
# backups to keep before older ones are pruned.
BACKUP_DIR=data/backups
BACKUP_RETENTION_DAYS=14

# Language
# "zh" (Traditional Chinese, default) or "en". Controls both the bot's own
# UI copy (internal/i18n) and the language Claude is asked to answer in for
# /check, /recommend, and chat. Anything unrecognized (including unset)
# falls back to "zh".
BOT_LANGUAGE=zh

# Web dashboard (Phase 5, see docs/phase-5-web-dashboard.md)
# Read-only. Leave blank/unset to disable (default) — do not expose this
# publicly, it has no login/HTTPS of its own by design; access it via
# Tailscale or an SSH tunnel to the VPS instead. Example:
#   WEB_ADDR=127.0.0.1:8090
WEB_ADDR=
